#: ../../rst/network/user_guide/network_best_practices_2.5.rst:150
msgid ""
"Certain network platforms, such as eos and ios, have the concept of "
"different privilege modes. Certain network modules, such as those that "
"modify system state including users, will only work in high privilege "
"states. Ansible version 2.5 added support for ``become`` when using "
"``connection: network_cli``. This allows privileges to be raised for the "
"specific tasks that need them. Adding ``become: yes`` and "
"``become_method: enable`` informs Ansible to go into privilege mode "
"before executing the task, as shown here:"
